Package: tdtR
Title: Read and Export Tucker-Davis Technologies Data from R
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("John", "Lee", email = "johnleenimh@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Provides a small R interface for reading Tucker-Davis Technologies
    (TDT) tank/block data through the Python 'tdt' package, formatting stream
    data for downstream analysis, and writing per-subject extraction metadata
    and stream exports. The package is intended for local and institutional use
    first, with package structure and checks kept close to CRAN and Bioconductor
    expectations.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    jsonlite,
    reticulate,
    rlang,
    tibble
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
